From 1ceaa3d2069c1f4c8849dd93cbf186d358ca5c59 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Peter Hirst <peter.hirst@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 10:11:34 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] feat: optional External Data Stream (JSON over local
 WebSocket)

Pushes decodes, rig status and logged QSOs to a configurable
ws://localhost endpoint so desktop companion tools (GridTracker,
JTAlert, QSO Predictor, loggers) can consume FT8web the way they
consume WSJT-X UDP today. Off by default; one-way; fire-and-forget
with auto-reconnect. Includes a reference Python bridge that
re-emits WSJT-X-protocol UDP datagrams for unmodified consumers.
